PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775192647
OL,3,CManned mission to Moon fires engines
OL,4,Cto leave Earth's orbit
OL,6,FNasa said the firing puts the crew "in
OL,7,Fa free return trajectory", enabling
OL,8,Fthem to use the Moon's gravity for the
OL,9,Freturn journey.
OL,11,FNasa administrator Jared Isaacman said
OL,12,Fon X: "Nominal translunar injection
OL,13,Fburn complete. The Artemis II crew is
OL,14,Fofficially on the way to the Moon.
OL,16,F"America is back in the business of
OL,17,Fsending astronauts to the Moon. This
OL,18,Ftime, farther than ever before."
OL,26,@nD@dOUoD@YO]tD@GOUxD@AOUzD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
