FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775192647
OL,3,CManned mission to Moon fires engines
OL,4,Cto leave Earth's orbit
OL,6,FNasa said preliminary reports
OL,7,Findicated the engine firing had gone
OL,8,Fwell and that Orion's main engine,
OL,9,Fwhich was due to burn for five minutes
OL,10,Fand 49 seconds, provides up to 6,000lb
OL,11,Fof thrust ` enough to accelerate a car
OL,12,Ffrom 0 to 60 mph in about 2.7 seconds.
OL,14,FThere was good news for the astronauts
OL,15,Fwhen they were able to fix issues with
OL,16,Fthe toilet, while controllers were
OL,17,Falso able to raise the cabin
OL,18,Ftemperature.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775192647
OL,3,CManned mission to Moon fires engines
OL,4,Cto leave Earth's orbit
OL,6,FThe Goonhilly Earth Station, near
OL,7,FHelston, in Cornwall, is helping to
OL,8,Ftrack the flight.
OL,10,FOrion will head around 4,000 miles
OL,11,Fbeyond the moon with a lunar flyby on
OL,12,FMonday the next major milestone which
OL,13,Fwill send the crew some 252,000 miles
OL,14,F(406,000 kilometres) into space before
OL,15,Freturning to Earth.
OL,17,FThe current record for the furthest
OL,18,Fspaceflight is about 248,000 miles,
OL,19,Fheld by members of the Apollo 13 lunar
OL,20,Fmission in 1970, which was hit by
OL,21,Ftechnical problems.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775192647
OL,3,CManned mission to Moon fires engines
OL,4,Cto leave Earth's orbit
OL,6,FWhile the astronauts will not touch
OL,7,Fdown on the Moon, the Artemis II
OL,8,Fmission paves the way for a future
OL,9,Flunar landing and also lays the
OL,10,Ffoundation to send a crew to Mars.
OL,12,FThe mission previously had to be
OL,13,Fpostponed by two months because of
OL,14,Fhydrogen fuel leaks and clogged helium
OL,15,Flines.
OL,17,FNasa is seeking to return a crew to
OL,18,Fthe lunar surface by 2028, before
OL,19,FChina does in about 2030.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/7
